Linux server (Ubuntu 20.04/22.04 or Debian-based)

Root or sudo access

Port 9090 (Prometheus) and 3000 (Grafana) open

üõ†Ô∏è Step 1: Install Prometheus
1.1 Create Prometheus user
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo useradd --no-create-home --shell /bin/false prometheus
1.2 Create directories
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo mkdir /etc/prometheus
sudo mkdir /var/lib/prometheus
1.3 Download Prometheus
bash
Copy
Edit
cd /tmp
curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/prometheus/prometheus/releases/latest \
  | grep browser_download_url \
  | grep linux-amd64.tar.gz \
  | cut -d '"' -f 4 \
  | wget -i -

tar -xvf prometheus-*-linux-amd64.tar.gz
cd prometheus-*-linux-amd64
1.4 Move binaries
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo cp prometheus /usr/local/bin/
sudo cp promtool /usr/local/bin/
sudo chown prometheus:prometheus /usr/local/bin/prometheus /usr/local/bin/promtool
1.5 Move config and consoles
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo cp -r consoles/ console_libraries/ /etc/prometheus/
sudo cp prometheus.yml /etc/prometheus/
sudo chown -R prometheus:prometheus /etc/prometheus /var/lib/prometheus
üìã Step 2: Create Prometheus systemd service
Create file:

bash
Copy
Edit
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/prometheus.service
Paste:

ini
Copy
Edit
[Unit]
Description=Prometheus
Wants=network-online.target
After=network-online.target

[Service]
User=prometheus
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/prometheus \
  --config.file=/etc/prometheus/prometheus.yml \
  --storage.tsdb.path=/var/lib/prometheus/ \
  --web.console.templates=/etc/prometheus/consoles \
  --web.console.libraries=/etc/prometheus/console_libraries

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
Start Prometheus
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable prometheus
sudo systemctl start prometheus
Test it:
Visit: http://<your_server_ip>:9090

üìä Step 3: Install Grafana
3.1 Add Grafana APT repo (for Debian/Ubuntu)
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo apt-get install -y software-properties-common
sudo add-apt-repository "deb https://packages.grafana.com/oss/deb stable main"
wget -q -O - https://packages.grafana.com/gpg.key | sudo apt-key add -
sudo apt-get update
3.2 Install Grafana
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo apt-get install -y grafana
3.3 Start and enable Grafana
bash
Copy
Edit
sudo systemctl start grafana-server
sudo systemctl enable grafana-server
Access it:
Open http://<your_server_ip>:3000

Login: admin / admin (change password on first login)

üîÑ Step 4: Connect Prometheus to Grafana
Login to Grafana

Go to Configuration ‚Üí Data Sources

Add data source ‚Üí Prometheus

URL: http://localhost:9090

Click Save & Test

‚úÖ You're Done!
Prometheus runs at: http://<ip>:9090

Grafana runs at: http://<ip>:3000

You can import dashboards for system monitoring or custom metrics.

